Costume Reference 7 - The Edwardians
Plays Publishers | 1978 | ISBN: 0823802280 | English | 84 pages | PDF | 8.6 MB

In this, the seventh of her eight-volume Costume Reference series, Marion Sichel traces costume changes for men, women and children in the period between the reigns of Edward VII and George V of England , to the end of World War I. In careful detail, she covers not only major items of clothing-coats, jackets, dresses, day and evening dress, formal and casual clothes, and outdoor wears but also accessories, hairstyles, beauty aids, and hat
